<subSubSection id="3B8B24AAFFF7FFF4FEAA23F0D831FB92" pageId="32" pageNumber="33" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="732E7721FFF7FFF4FEAA23F0D831FB92" blockId="32.[264,1324,283,1030]" pageId="32" pageNumber="33">
<emphasis id="41E5AB33FFF7FFF4FEAA23F0DBB3FC81" bold="true" box="[312,445,763,789]" pageId="32" pageNumber="33">Etymology</emphasis>
. Named for Jack Clayton Hall (
<number id="C5596506FFF7FFF4FCAA23F7D97DFC82" box="[824,883,764,790]" pageId="32" pageNumber="33" value="1925.0">1925</number>
–) who has encouraged the junior author to work diligently on 
<taxonomicName id="B4910CA2FFF7FFF4FDCF222FD8F9FCAA" box="[605,759,804,830]" class="Insecta" family="Bombyliidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="32" pageNumber="33" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Bombyliidae</taxonomicName>
, even after the senior author’s premature retirement in 
<number id="C5596506FFF7FFF4FEF82247DBABFCF2" box="[362,421,844,870]" pageId="32" pageNumber="33" value="1988.0">1988</number>
from the University of California at Riverside. Jack began the work on this revision and his sudden retirement forced him to abort a nearly finished study of this subgenus of 
<taxonomicName id="B4910CA2FFF7FFF4FEE92297D819FC22" box="[379,535,924,950]" class="Insecta" family="Bombyliidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="32" pageNumber="33" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Bombyliidae</taxonomicName>
. It is the pleasure of the junior author to belatedly complete this study and honor him with a patronymic species that was not a part of his original revisionary notes on the subgenus.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
